         <abstract>
            <p>The analogy between Plato's notion of khora in the Timaeus and Derrida's notion of khora as a surname for différence should include the mythic elements described in the opening verses of Genesis. The elements are not an irrational chaos but provide a principle of indeterminacy that gives creation unprogrammability, risk, and the possibility of the event.</p>
         </abstract>
